        fruit: "https://assets.babycenter.com/ims/2020/11/21-weeks-carrot_wide.jpg?width=722",
        size: "Your carrot-sized cutie is now a little over 10 1/2 inches from head to heel and weighs about 14 ounces.",
        development: `Your baby has working taste buds and can taste what you eat when they swallow your amniotic fluid. Your baby's sucking reflex is starting to develop, and your baby can suck their thumb. Smooth, gorgeous skin is in your baby's future – but for now, their skin is wrinkled and translucent. It appears red because of visible blood vessels.`,
        mom: `You're more prone to varicose veins now. As your pregnancy progresses, the weight of your uterus puts increasing pressure on the veins in your legs. Braxton Hicks are "practice" uterine contractions that are mostly infrequent, irregular, and painless. They start early in pregnancy, but you probably won't start feeling them until around 21 weeks. (Some women never notice them, and that's okay, too.). It's most common to have Braxton Hicks contractions at the end of the day, when you're dehydrated or have a full bladder, or during or after physical activities including sex. `,
        pictureus: "https://www.netmums.com/wp-content/uploads/netmums/2023/08/060c53dfd3a6a07e26af94388fc3c101-615x410.jpg",
