        fruit: "Now that your appetite has likely returned (perhaps stronger than ever), you might be having intense cravings. Most women will crave at least one specific food during pregnancy, and many crave a variety of different foods. ",
        size: "Your baby is now about 12 1/2 inches long from head to heel and weighs nearly 1 1/2 pounds.",
        development: `Respiratory sacs at the tips of the smallest branches of your baby's lungs are growing and multiplying, adding more surface area for the exchange of oxygen and carbon dioxide.Your baby cuts a pretty lean figure at this point, but their body is filling out proportionally, and soon they'll start to plump up. Their skin is still thin and translucent. Tiny eyebrows grew on your baby's face just a few weeks ago. Now your baby may practice working their facial muscles and raising them.`,
        mom: `If you're experiencing new skin symptoms, like itchiness, hyperpigmentation, raised bumps, or hives, check in with your doctor or midwife. Most rashes during pregnancy are related to allergies, contact dermatitis (contact with an irritant), or skin infections – they're not caused by pregnancy. During the second trimester, some women experience spotting or light bleeding during pregnancy. This could be caused by changes to your cervix, inflammation, or a benign cervical polyp. Spotting during the second trimester is typically harmless. However, if you experience regular, heavier bleeding, seek medical attention right away. Dramatic mood swings may have faded at 24 weeks pregnant – but it's perfectly normal to have them during the second trimester. `,
