        mom: "If your lower back is aching lately, you can thank both your growing uterus and hormonal changes that loosen your joints and ligaments. Roughly 60 percent of pregnant women have lower-back pain, which can make it hard to sleep or perform daily tasks. If your lower back is aching lately, you can thank both your growing uterus and hormonal changes that loosen your joints and ligaments. Roughly 60 percent of pregnant women have lower-back pain, which can make it hard to sleep or perform daily tasks.",
